			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: The deep shard, vt key<a name="42958"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 28 04 2:19 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>You can get the shard off anything in the zone. They drop most commonly from the thought horror types (green tentacle heads). They drop FAR more frequently back towards the SSraa zone than they do on the SH side of the chasm (1 in every 3 kills or so back by Ssraa).
<br />

<br />
If you are trying them solo, I would advise lulling (or invising) to the chasm. there is usually one see-invis mutant or shroom on the way, so take your time &amp; lull the see-invis one(s) before re-invising on your way. There are plenty of nice camping spots (and CRs are not too tedious). Do not try to cross the big white bridge. It is not real and you will fall into the Abyss. Single pull the young thought leeches to the wall and dispach them as best as you are able. Thought horrors are lullable, snarable, &amp; slowable but cannot be mezzed. 
<br />

<br />
I personally prefer the large open area in front of the false bridge. Once you break the spawn, you can actually chant-kite if you're careful. Assonant, DoT, DoT, DoT is recommended til you learn the area. Remember, you can chant- kite in a straight line just as well as a circle. Just make sure not to fall in the Abyss when changing directions.
<br />

<br />
I would not advise crossing the invisible bridge if you are soloing. Critters get radically harder on that side and most cast, have pets, and/or have a boatload o hp even though they al look identical to the ones on the SH side. Unless you are very well equipped (or a Necro/BST) , I would not imagine soloing is a realistic option on SSraa side.
<br />

<br />
Hope that is of some use,
<br />

<br />
-Savidge Rhythums
<br />
-Quellious</span></td>
