				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: The deep shard, vt key<a name="43497"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 1 04 5:07 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Just want to second Lumi's post above - I've done this shard for three characters and each time I've used that same small cluster of thought horrors.  
<br />

<br />
Fortunately, since I did this with a shaman each time, they don't even need to be lulled. <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />  They'll come single if you pull them in the right order.  I don't recall if they gated or not, I always fought pretty close to their spawn points.
<br />

<br />
You can pull five, I think, without getting 2 at a time, the respawn rate is pretty quick, and you'll probably have a shard in an hour or so.
<br />

<br />
I've never seen a shard off a non-thought-horror in this zone, and I did about 3 AA's grinding on Ancient Shriekers for fungoid sap.
<br />

<br />
As for getting to the other side of the invis bridge, when I've done it as a bard, I just trained to the gorge, jumped with divine aura song up and faded at the bottom - you can walk up the other side.
<br />

<br />
Much quicker and fun.
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
